{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-03435/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-03435"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:34:35"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["full shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["eye-level"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["two shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A woman stands still in a moonlit room while a man kneels behind her, pinning the hem of her full skirt."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03435/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-03435","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03435/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-03435"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03435/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03435/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03435/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03435/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03435/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03435/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03435/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03435/canvas/1/08c42f25-6d10-4636-bdbd-a831f7f507ef","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T15:13:51.720Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>In the world of <em>Phantom Thead</em>, sex is sublimated into dressmaking (along with eating). The way Alma describes how Reynolds is willing to “start again” after they go to bed late may as well refer to sex. Alma, though, prides herself in how she can stand endlessly, taking part in Reynolds’s practices and preferences.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03435/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:864.3876177658143,88.42530282637959,205.43741588156115,139.54239569313597"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03435/canvas/1/f549b977-486e-4e2c-9094-f1be2b3fe277","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T15:14:08.202Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>In this shot, Alma is contrasted with the statue in the background, both in the way she stands (mostly) still and in the white of her clothing. As before, this framing plays on the Pygmalion myth. Most well-known from Ovid’s <em>Metamorphoses</em>, the story traces how the titular sculptor falls in love with one of his statues who is granted life by Aphrodite. Reynolds sees his art as giving life to form, to inorganic matter (cloth) in the shape of dresses. Here, he resembles a sculptor carving or giving shape to his love, Alma.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03435/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:1085.3297442799462,79.38088829071344,107.24091520861384,310.09421265141316"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03435/canvas/1/15c829af-60b1-4dee-bc93-48d447037b55","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T15:14:26.037Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>In another contrast of light and dark, the gloomy night interacts with the mood lighting of Reynolds’s studio, even casting a blue tint onto the foreground of the shot. Like Reynolds and Alma themselves in their relationship, his space incorporates opposites.</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03435/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:549.1251682368776,52.24764468371475,293.2974427994616,436.7160161507402"}}}]}]}]}